[assistant] Adjusted the test so Jackson cannot bind the property through a matching backing field.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - Even with field auto-detection disabled, the private field named `values` was still being associated with the logical property `values`, so Jackson chose `FieldProperty`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Renamed the backing field from `values` to `entries`.
[assistant] - Kept the public getter as `getValues()`, making the logical property getter-only and forcing Jackson to use `SetterlessProperty`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `3994503d7 Add parquet jackson setterless property coverage`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests locally.
